By default, `width` + `padding` + `border` = Total Width. This is annoying!

## box-sizing: border-box

Includes padding and border IN the specific width.

```css
* {
  box-sizing: border-box;
}
```

If you set `width: 200px` and `padding: 20px`, the total width stays 200px (content shrinks to 160px). Most modern frameworks use this!
